COMMENT - A histidine residue embedded in the canonical B<sub>12</sub>-binding DxHxxG motif in methylmalonyl-CoA mutase serves as the lower axial ligand to the cobalt, which is bound in the "base-off/His-on" state |CITS: [Padmakumar95][8805541]|. This structure depicts this L-histidine residue in the <i>apo</i> enzyme.
ABBREV-NAME - methylmalonyl-CoA mutase
//
