UNIQUE-ID - Elongation-factor-2
TYPES - Polypeptides
COMMON-NAME - elongation factor 2
COMMENT - The translation elongation factor 2 (eEF2), is found in archaea and all eukaryotes. Elongation factors are proteins that function at the ribosome, during protein synthesis, to facilitate translational elongation from formation of the first to the last peptide bond of a growing polypeptide.
/
/Archaeaons and eukaryotes have similar elongation factors, which are different from the bacterial ones. 
/
/Eukaryotic/archeal elongation factors include eEF-1A and eEF-1B, eEF-2, and EIF5A. Bacterial factors include EF-Tu, EF-Ts, EF-G, and EF-P.
ABBREV-NAME - eEF-2
