TYPES - Polyketide-ACP-Proteins
COMMON-NAME - (<i>S</i>)-2-methylbutanoyl-[2-methylbutanoate polyketide synthase]
COMMENT - LovF is a 277 kDa diketide synthase involved in the biosynthesis of lovastatin. LovF synthesizes the |FRAME: CPD-16943| side chain, which is subsequently transferred by the dissociated acyltransferase LovD to the C8-hydroxyl of |FRAME: CPD-16908| to yield the complete natural product, |FRAME: CPD-16924|.
/
/The enzyme utilizes acetyl-CoA, malonyl-CoA, NADPH, and SAM to yield R-methylbutanoyl-S-LovF, in a process that involves a single condensation reaction followed by &alpha;-methylation, &beta;-ketoreduction, dehydration, and &alpha;,&beta; enoyl reduction reactions at the active sites of the various catalytic domains |CITS: [21069965]|.
