UNIQUE-ID - Sulfur-Carrier-Proteins-TusE
TYPES - Polypeptides
COMMON-NAME - a TusE sulfur-carrier protein
COMMENT - TusE functions as a sulfur mediator during synthesis of 2-thiouridine of the modified wobble base mnm<sup>5</sup>s<sup>2</sup>U in tRNA. TusE directly interacts with both the TusBCD complex and the MnmA-tRNA complex, but not with tRNA itself |CITS: [16387657]|.
/
/2-thiouridine formation <i>in vitro</i> is greatly enhanced in the presence of TusE. TusE is labeled by <sup>35</sup>S sulfur during 2-thiouridine formation <i>in vitro</i> |CITS: [16387657]|.
/
/A <i>tusE</i> deletion mutant lacks mnm<sup>5</sup>s<sup>2</sup>U, accumulates mnm<sup>5</sup>U and has a growth defect.  The cysteine residue C108 is required for sulfur transfer |CITS: [16387657]|.
ABBREV-NAME - TusE
//
