UNIQUE-ID - Phenylurea-Herbicides
TYPES - Herbicides
TYPES - Phenylureas
COMMON-NAME - a phenylurea herbicide
COMMENT - The phenylurea herbicides, first discovered and marketed in the mid-20th century, are some of the most important classes of herbicides. They have been used in a variety of agricultural and urban environments around the world. Due to their relatively high water solubilities some phenylurea herbicides and their metabolites have been detected as contaminants of groundwater, streams, lakes, and seawater in different areas worldwide. In addition, ecotoxicological data show that phenylurea herbicides and their main metabolites are environmental hazards and are carcinogenic to animals and humans |CITS: [2279779][8402576]|.
//
