UNIQUE-ID - Egg-glycoprotein-Gp41
TYPES - Polypeptides
TYPES - Modified-Proteins
COMMON-NAME - egg glycoprotein Gp41
COMMENT - Animal eggs contain several glycoproteins involved in species-specific sperm binding, induction of the acrosome reaction and prevention of post-fertilization polyspermy. In mammals these proteins form the zona pellucida - a glycoprotein membrane surrounding the plasma membrane of the oocyte. The mammalian zona pellucida consists of four glycoproteins - ZP1, ZP2, ZP3 and ZP4. ZP3 is responsible for species-specific sperm binding.
/
/The homolog of ZP3 in frogs is called Gp43 |CITS: [9352194]|. Gp43 is synthesized in an <i>apo</i> inactive form, and is cleaved to form the active form, known as Gp41, by |FRAME: EC-3.4.21.120| |CITS: [10084976]|.
