/
/The word phenol is also used to refer to any compound that contains a six-membered aromatic ring, bonded directly to a hydroxyl group (-OH). Thus, |FRAME: Phenols phenols| are a class of organic compounds of which the |FRAME: PHENOL "phenol compound"| is the simplest member.
