UNIQUE-ID - Prokaryotic-ubiquitin-like-proteins
TYPES - Polypeptides
COMMON-NAME - a prokaryotic ubiquitin-like protein
COMMENT - Prokaryotic ubiquitin-like protein (Pup) is a functional analog of |FRAME: Ubiquitins ubiquitin|, described from members of the |FRAME: TAX-1762|.
/
/Pup essentially serves the same function as |FRAME: Ubiquitins ubiquitin|. It attaches to specific lysine residues of substrate proteins by forming isopeptide bonds. The conjugated proteins are recognized by the Mycobacterium proteasomal ATPase (Mpa), which delivers them to the 20S proteasome, coupling ATP hydrolysis with proteasomal degradation.
//
UNIQUE-ID - Mycoredoxins
TYPES - Polypeptides
COMMON-NAME - a mycoredoxin
COMMENT - Mycoredoxin is a mycothiol-dependent reductase identified in Mycobacteria that couples the reducing power of |FRAME: CPD1G-2| to redox active proteins |CITS: [22970802]|.
/
/Mycoredoxin acts as an oxidoreductase exclusively linked to the mycothiol electron transfer pathway and can reduce S-mycothiolated mixed disulfides. It contains a thioredoxin fold and a mycothiol-binding site. Mycothiol is covalently attached to a nucleophilic cysteine, forming |FRAME: Mycothiol-mycoredoxin-mixed-disulfides| |CITS: [22970802]|.
//
UNIQUE-ID - Protein-C
