UNIQUE-ID - Steroid-Hormones
TYPES - Steroids
TYPES - Hormones
COMMON-NAME - a steroid hormone
COMMENT - Steroid hormones are steroids that act as hormones. Steroid hormones are divided into five groups based on the receptors to which they bind: |FRAME: Glucocorticoids glucocorticoids|, |FRAME: Mineralocorticoids mineralocorticoids|, |FRAME: Androgens androgens|, |FRAME: Steroidal-Estrogens "steroidal estrogens"|, and |FRAME: Progestogens progestogens|. Certain vitamin D derivatives (e.g. |FRAME: CALCITRIOL|) are sometimes considered a sixth steroid hormone group.
/
/The natural steroid hormones of mammals are generally synthesized from cholesterol in the gonads and adrenal glands.
//
