UNIQUE-ID - Ubiquitin-carrier-proteins-E2
TYPES - Polypeptides
COMMON-NAME - ubiquitin-conjugating enzyme E2
SYNONYMS - ubiquitin-carrier enzyme E2
SYNONYMS - ubiquitin-carrier protein E2
SYNONYMS - a ubiquitin-conjugating enzyme
SYNONYMS - a ubiquitin-carrier enzyme
COMMENT - The ubiquitin-conjugating enzymes E2 (also called ubiquitin-carrier-proteins, E2 enzymes, or ubiquitin-conjugating enzymes), perform the second step in the ubiquitination reaction. 
/
/The activity of the enzyme starts with the transfer of |FRAME: Ubiquitins ubiquitin| from an |FRAME: Ubiquitin-activating-proteins-E1 E1|-ubiquitin complex to a catalytic L-cysteine residue at the active site by transesterification. Once loaded with ubiquitin, the E2 enzyme binds one of several |FRAME: E3-ubiquitin-carrier-proteins "E3 ubiquitin-carrier proteins"| (or E3 enzymes) via a structurally conserved binding region. The E3 enzyme also binds the target protein substrate, and catalyzes the transfer of the ubiquitin from the E2 cysteine to a lysine residue on the target protein.
/
