UNIQUE-ID - CPD-12146
TYPES - Radicals
TYPES - Quinones
TYPES - In-Situ-Cofactors
COMMON-NAME - copper-complexed cysteinyltyrosyl radical cofactor
COMMENT - |FRAME:CPD-12146 "Copper-complexed cysteinyltyrosyl radical"| is a cofactor of |FRAME: MONOMER-15357| (|FRAME: GALACTOSE-OXIDASE-RXN "EC 1.1.3.9"|). This cofactor involves a thioether bond between an |FRAME: TYR| and an |FRAME: CYS| in the enzyme's polypeptide chain, and an |FRAME: CU+2| atom. The active site also contains a free radical on the tyrosine |CITS: [2002850][7929198]|.
/
/The copper site, which is not shown in the structure below, has five ligands in square pyramidal coordination. Tyr 272, His 496, His 581 and an acetate ion form an almost perfect square around the copper ion. The fifth ligand, which is axial, is Tyr 495 (amino acid numbering is bassed on the enzyme from |FRAME: TAX-5132|) |CITS: [2002850]|.
