UNIQUE-ID - Excited-blue-fluorescent-proteins
TYPES - Protein-Small-Molecule-Complexes
COMMON-NAME - an excited state blue fluorescent protein
SYNONYMS - an excited state BFP
SYNONYMS - BFP*
COMMENT - The blue fluorescent proteins of jellyfish are formed from the calcium-binding photoprotein |FRAME: Aequorins aequorin| following the bioluminescent reaction. They are complexes of Ca<sup>2+</sup> -bound |FRAME: Apoaequorins <i>apo</i>-aequorin| polypeptide |CITS: [4393938]| complexed with a |FRAME: OXIDIZED-OPLOPHORUS-LUCIFERIN coelenteramide| molecule |CITS: [15527769][16545379]|.
/
/The protein demonstrates blue fluorescence, and interestingly, can also act as a luciferase, catalyzing the oxidation of coelenterazine by molecular oxygen to emit light |CITS: [17254548][19549504]|.
/
/Removal of the Ca<sup>2+</sup> ions by treatment with EDTA converts the protein to a green-emitting fluorescent protein |CITS: [16545379]|.
//
