UNIQUE-ID - ACTINOMYCIN
TYPES - Antibiotics
COMMON-NAME - an actinomycin
COMMENT - The |FRAME: ACTINOMYCIN actinomycins| are a family of bicyclic chromopeptide lactones with strong antineoplastic activity that are produced by various streptomycete strains |CITS: [16588723][18910692][    24543239]|. The first actinomycin was isolated from |FRAME: TAX-1890| in 1940, and was the first antibiotic obtained in pure form from an actinomycete |CITS: [Waksman40]|. |FRAME: ACTINOMYCIN-D "Actinomycin D"| was the first antibiotic shown to have anti-cancer activity |CITS: [13112124][4130354]|, and was approved as an anticancer drug in 1964, making it one of the oldest anticancer drugs. Actinomycin D inhibits transcription by binding DNA at the transcription initiation complex and preventing elongation of RNA chain by RNA polymerase |CITS: [ 2410919]|.
/
/A common feature of all actinomycins is the chromophoric moiety |FRAME: CPD-18447|, which is a unique phenoxazinone dicarboxylic acid to which two pentapeptide lactone rings are attached with amide linkages |CITS: [15395378][13505348][13790233]|.
//
