UNIQUE-ID - LarE
TYPES - Polypeptides
COMMON-NAME - a LarE protein
COMMENT - LarE is an enzyme involved in the biosynthesis of the nickel-pincer cofactor |FRAME: CPD-18436|. It was first characxterized from L|FRAME: TAX-1590|.
/
/LarE catalyzes a complex reaction comprising several steps. First, it adenylates pyridinium-3,5-biscarboxylic acid mononucleotide (P2CMN) or pyridinium-3-thiocarboxylate-5-carboxylate mononucleotide (PCTMN), and covalently binds the adenylated intermediate to an intrinsic cysteine residue.
/In a third step PCTMN or pyridinium-3,5-bisthiocarboxylate mononucleotide (P2TMN) is liberated, leaving a dehydroalanine moiety attached to the protein. The cysteine residue is not regenerated <i>in vivo</i> |CITS: [27114550]|.
//
