UNIQUE-ID - Apo-beta-Allophycocyanins
TYPES - Polypeptides
COMMON-NAME - an <i>apo</i>-[allophycocyanin &beta;-subunit]
SYNONYMS - <i>apo</i>-ApcB
COMMENT - |FRAME: Phycoerythrocyanins Phycoerythrocyanins| are members of the |FRAME: Phycobiliproteins phycobiliproteins|, which are components of the photosynthetic light-harvesting antenna complexes of |FRAME: TAX-1117| and some algae (|FRAME: TAX-2763 rhodophytes|, |FRAME: TAX-3027 cryptomonads|, and |FRAME: TAX-38254 glaucocystophytes|) that capture light energy and pass it on to |FRAME: Chlorophylls chlorophylls| during photosynthesis. They increase the efficiency of photosynthesis by collecting light energy at wavelengths over which chlorophyll absorbs poorly.
/
/Allophycocyanins, which are found in in cyanobacteria and red algae, have a characteristic blue color, and absorb red light around 650 nm. Like other |FRAME: Phycobiliproteins phycobiliproteins| allophycocyanins are composed of two different types of subunits, forming an (&alpha;&beta;)<sub>6</sub> structure. Both subunits covalently bind a single |FRAME: Phycocyanobilins phycocyanobilin| chromophore to a cysteine residue at position 84 |CITS: [7783202]|.
/
/
/Attachment of the |FRAME: Phycocyanobilins phycocyanobilin| chromophore to the Cys-84 position of both the &alpha; and &beta; subunits of |FRAME: Allophycocyanins allophycocyanin| is catalyzed by the |FRAME: MONOMER-18986 "CpcS lyase"| |CITS: [17895251]|.
ABBREV-NAME - allophycocyanin &beta;-subunit
