UNIQUE-ID - All-holo-ACPs
TYPES - All-ACPs
TYPES - Modified-Proteins
COMMON-NAME - all <i>holo</i>-acyl carrier proteins
COMMENT - Acyl carrier proteins exist as either a distinct domain within a large multifunctional protein, or as discrete soluble single-domain proteins.
/
/Acyl-carrier proteins are synthesized in their |FRAME: apo-ACP "<i>apo</i> inactive form"|, and are activated by attachment of a |FRAME: PANTETHEINE-P| moiety, removed from |FRAME: CO-A|, to an |FRAME: SER| residue, in a reaction catalyzed by |FRAME: EC-2.7.8.7| (4'-phosphopantetheinyl transferase) |CITS: [18059524]|.
/
/This high-level class describes the <i>holo</i> form all the acyl-carrier proteins, which consist of the |FRAME: Fatty-Acid-Synthase-ACPs "acyl-carrier proteins (ACPs) of fatty acid synthases"|, |FRAME: Polyketide-ACP-Proteins "ACPs of polyketide synthases"| (PKSs), |FRAME: Peptidyl-Carrier-Proteins "peptidyl carrier proteins"| (PCPs) and |FRAME: Aryl-Carrier-Proteins "aryl carrier proteins"| of |FRAME: Non-ribosomal-peptide-synthetases "non-ribosomal peptide synthetases"| (NRPSs), and |FRAME: ACP "soluble, standalone acyl-carrier proteins"|.
ABBREV-NAME - a <i>holo</i> acyl-carrier protein
