/X-ray structures of retinoid-binding proteins have shown that bound retinol is sandwiched inside a 10-stranded, anti-parallel &beta;-barrel with the alcohol moiety situated innermost and in close contact with a glutamine side chain, forming a hydrogen bond. The bound retinol has a 6-<i>S</i>-trans conformation |CITS: [7683727][8487303][8839926]|.
