COMMENT - Glycerolipids are lipids that contain a |FRAME: GLYCEROL| backbone to which at least one fatty acyl group is esterified. If a phosphate group is ester-linked to the terminal carbon of the |FRAME: GLYCEROL| backbone, the compound is classified as |FRAME: Phosphoglycerides|.
