UNIQUE-ID - 50S-Ribosomal-subunit-protein-L16
TYPES - Polypeptides
COMMON-NAME - 50S ribosomal subunit protein L16
COMMENT - The L16 protein is a late assembly component of the 50S subunit of the ribosome; ribosomes lacking L16 are translationally active |CITS: [2204629]|.  L2 is required for assembly of L16 into the 50S subunit |CITS: [2211695]|.
/
/L16 interacts with tRNA |CITS: [6352325][6363130][2182127]| and can be crosslinked to aminoacylated tRNA in the A and P site |CITS: [386278][8524654]|.  Conserved residues within L16 were shown to be involved in the translocation of tRNA from the A to the P site |CITS: [24186064]|.  L16 is located within 21 &Aring; of nucleotide C2475 of 23S rRNA, near the peptidyltransferase center |CITS: [7529559]|.  L16 and a histidine residue within the N-terminal domain of L16 may be important for the correct conformation of the peptidyltransferase center |CITS: [6254759][3549294][3297687]|.  L16 is important for release factor 2-dependent peptidyl-tRNA hydrolysis |CITS: [6355096]|.  The antibiotics chloramphenicol |CITS: [4365366][4599619]| and virginiamycin S |CITS: [95947]| interact with L16 within the ribosome.
/
/L16 is one of six ribosomal proteins that is completely lost from ribosomes in post-stationary cells |CITS: [6201363]|.
/
/The N-terminal methionine of L16 appears to be methylated |CITS: [786730][323502]|, and additional posttranslational modifications of the protein are present |CITS: [10094780][22649682]|.  These include phosphorylation |CITS: [17938405][19469554]| as well as hydroxylation of the Arg81 residue by |FRAME: CPLX0-8112| |CITS: [23103944]|.
/
/L16 has RNA chaperone-like activity in an <i>in vitro trans</i>-splicing assay |CITS: [15525706]| as well as protein chaperone activity |CITS: [19071121]|.
/
