COMMENT - |FRAME: EC-2.7.2.18| (Fak) consists of a dimeric ATP-binding protein (FakA) and a fatty acid-binding protein (FakB). The first step in the reaction is the binding of FakB to FakA. The fatty acid bound to FakB is then phosphorylated
/by FakA, and the acyl-phosphate-bound FakB is released from the complex. In the presence of an exchangeable fatty acid pool in the cell membrane, the acyl-phosphate bound to FakB exchanges with a fatty acid to regenerate the substrate for FakA.
//
