UNIQUE-ID - Rhd
TYPES - Polypeptides
COMMON-NAME - Rhd sulfur-carrier protein
SYNONYMS - Rhd rhodanese
COMMENT - Rhd is a small protein (11.9 kDa) with a single rhodanese domain that can carry a sulfane sulfur on an active site L-cysteine residue |CITS: [24648525]|.
/
/Rhd is the first member of the cytoplasmic sulfur trafficking network involved in dissimilatory sulfur oxidation by sulfur oxidizing bacteria that form periplasmic sulfur globules. The natural substrate for the enzyme is the low molecular weight persulfide that serves as a carrier for sulfur from the periplasmic sulfur globules to the cytoplasm. The sulfur is then transferred to the next member of the sulfur-transfer chain, |FRAME: TusA| |CITS: [24648525]|.
