TYPES - Polypeptides
TYPES - Modified-Proteins
COMMON-NAME - a [C-phycocyanin &alpha;-subunit]-Cys<sup>84</sup>-phycocyanobilin
COMMENT - |FRAME: Phycocyanins Phycocyanins| are members of the |FRAME: Phycobiliproteins phycobiliproteins|, which are components of the photosynthetic light-harvesting antenna complexes of |FRAME: TAX-1117| and some algae (|FRAME: TAX-2763 rhodophytes|, |FRAME: TAX-3027 cryptomonads|, and |FRAME: TAX-38254 glaucocystophytes|) that capture light energy and pass it on to |FRAME: Chlorophylls chlorophylls| during photosynthesis. They increase the efficiency of photosynthesis by collecting light energy at wavelengths over which chlorophyll absorbs poorly.
/
/|FRAME: Phycocyanins Phycocyanins|, which are found in |FRAME: TAX-1117|, have a characteristic light blue color, and absorb orange and red light, particularly near 620 nm. Two types of phycocyanin are known: |FRAME: C-Phycocyanins| binds only |FRAME: Phycocyanobilins phycocyanobilin| as the sole chromophore, while |FRAME: R-Phycocyanins| binds both |FRAME: Phycocyanobilins phycocyanobilin| and |FRAME: Phycoerythrobilins phycoerythrobilin| |CITS: [16742564]|.
/
/Like other |FRAME: Phycobiliproteins phycobiliproteins|, phycocyanins are composed of two types of subunits, named &alpha; and &beta;. In the case of |FRAME: C-Phycocyanins|, both subunits bind a |FRAME: Phycocyanobilins phycocyanobilin| chromophore. The chromophore is attached to the protein by a dedicated lyase enzyme, encoded by the <i>cpcE</i> and <i>cpcF</i> genes |CITS: [21553904][16519690]|.
ABBREV-NAME - a [C-phycocyanin &alpha;-subunit-Cys<sup>84</sup>]-phycocyanobilin
