UNIQUE-ID - 30S-ribosomal-subunit-protein-S18
TYPES - Polypeptides
COMMON-NAME - a 30S ribosomal subunit protein S18
COMMENT - The S18 protein is a component of the 30S subunit of the ribosome.
/
/The N-terminal alanine residue of S18 is acetylated by the |FRAME: EG10850-MONOMER RimI| enzyme |CITS: [6991870][10094780]|.  N-terminal acetylation of S18 and S5 correlates with correct folding of the platform and central pseudoknot domains of 16S rRNA |CITS: [24207057]|.
/
/S18 interacts with the central domain of 16S rRNA; the interaction is dependent on S8 and S15 |CITS: [6208366][2449359][2459389]|.  S18 may be involved in binding of aminoacyl-tRNA to the P site of the ribosome |CITS: [4585975]|.  S18 is photoaffinity labeled by puromycin, an analog of the 3' end of aminoacylated tRNA |CITS: [8034577]|.
/
/S18 was also shown to crosslink to IF3 |CITS: [7000779][7020604]|, IF1 |CITS: [6349681]| and 4.5S RNA |CITS: [16043501]|.
/
/Expression analysis of <i>rpsF</i>p indicates that it may be autoregulated by one or more of its operon components |CITS: [23292777]|.  Coexpressed S6:S18 were found to bind to the <i>rpsF</i> 5'-UTR in a region with structural similarity to their binding site in 16S rRNA |CITS: [23980204]|.  The S6:S18 complex was shown to repress translation of <i>rpsF</i> |CITS: [26447183]|.
/
/Review: |CITS: [22649682]|
//
