UNIQUE-ID - Beta-phosphoglucomutase
TYPES - Polypeptides
COMMON-NAME - a &beta;-phosphoglucomutase
COMMENT - |FRAME: EC-5.4.2.6| catalyzes the interconversion of the |FRAME: CPD-448| and
/|FRAME: GLC-6-P| isomers.  
/
/The enzyme is active only when an aspartate residue at the active site is phosphorylated. The enzyme is able to autophosphorylate itself with its substrate ß-D-glucose 1-phosphate inefficiently. Even though this phosphorylation is slow, a single turnover is required for activation. Once the phosphorylated enzyme is formed, it generates the reaction intermediate |FRAME: GLUCOSE-16-DIPHOSPHATE|, which can be used to phosphorylate the enzyme in subsequent cycles efficiently |CITS: [16784233]|.
//
