UNIQUE-ID - Tubulins
TYPES - Polypeptides
COMMON-NAME - a tubulin
COMMENT - The broad term "tubulin" refers to any member of the tubulin protein superfamily of globular proteins. 
/Six members of the tubulin superfamily have been described in eukaryotes, although not all are present in all species |CITS: [25169981]|. &alpha;- and &beta;-tubulins polymerize into microtubules, a major component of the eukaryotic cytoskeleton |CITS: [25788699]|.
/
/While tubulin has been thought to be specific to eukaryotes, several prokaryotic tubulin-like proteins have been discovered  |CITS: [9628483][12486237][17510284][22458654]|.
