UNIQUE-ID - SAMP-activating-proteins-E1
TYPES - Polypeptides
COMMON-NAME - SAMP ubiquitin-activating enzyme
SYNONYMS - SAMP-activating protein E1
SYNONYMS - SAMP-activating enzyme E1
SYNONYMS - SAMP-activating E1 enzyme
COMMENT - SAMP-activating enzymes, also known as E1-like enzymes, catalyze the first step in the SAMPylation reaction. The E1 enzyme binds ATP-Mg2+ and |FRAME: SAMP SAMP|, and catalyzes SAMP C-terminal acyl adenylation. A catalytic L-cysteine residue of the E1 enzyme then attacks the SAMP-AMP complex through acyl substitution, creating a thioester bond and an AMP leaving group.
/
/This active form of SAMP, bound to the E1 enzyme, is transferred to its target proteins by a process that is still not fully understood.
