TYPES - Polypeptides
TYPES - Modified-Proteins
COMMON-NAME - a [phycoerythrocyanin &beta;-subunit]-Cys<sup>155</sup>-phycocyanobilin
SYNONYMS - a [phycoerythrocyanin &beta;-subunit Cys-155]-PCB
COMMENT - |FRAME: Phycoerythrocyanins Phycoerythrocyanins| are members of the |FRAME: Phycobiliproteins phycobiliproteins|, which are components of the photosynthetic light-harvesting antenna complexes of |FRAME: TAX-1117| and some algae (|FRAME: TAX-2763 rhodophytes|, |FRAME: TAX-3027 cryptomonads|, and |FRAME: TAX-38254 glaucocystophytes|) that capture light energy and pass it on to |FRAME: Chlorophylls chlorophylls| during photosynthesis. They increase the efficiency of photosynthesis by collecting light energy at wavelengths over which chlorophyll absorbs poorly.
/
/|FRAME: Phycoerythrocyanins Phycoerythrocyanins|, which are found in in some cyanobacteria, have a characteristic magenta color, and an absorption maximum around 575 nm. Like other |FRAME: Phycobiliproteins phycobiliproteins|, they are composed from two types of subunits. The &alpha; chain (encoded by the <i>pecA</i> gene) contains one molecule of the violet chromophore |FRAME: Phycoviolobilins phycoviolobilin|, which is covalently attached at Cys-84, and the &beta; subunit (encoded by the <i>pecB</i> gene) contains two molecules of the blue chromophore |FRAME: Phycocyanobilins phycocyanobilin|, which are covalently attached at Cys-84 and -155, respectively.
/
/The |FRAME: Phycoviolobilins phycoviolobilin| chromophore is synthesized by the attachment of free |FRAME: CPD-17222| to the &alpha; subunit (PecA) followed by its isomerization to |FRAME: Phycoviolobilins phycoviolobilin|, catalyzed by the |FRAME: CPLX-8936| enzyme (PecEF) |CITS: [10708746][19182270]|.
/
/Attachment of the |FRAME: Phycocyanobilins phycocyanobilin| chromophore to the Cys-84 position of the &beta; subunit is catalyzed by |FRAME: MONOMER-18987| |CITS: [17895251]|.
//
