UNIQUE-ID - NifEN
TYPES - Protein-Complexes
COMMON-NAME - a NifEN protein complex
SYNONYMS - an <i>apo</i>-NifEN protein complex
COMMENT - The NifEN protein complex functions as a scaffold in the biosynthesis of the |FRAME: CPD-41| of [MoFe]-nitrogenases, and serves as a central node to which the |FRAME: CPD-18407| precursor, molybdenum, and |FRAME: HOMO-CIT| converge to complete the assembly of the cofactor.
/
/The protein complex shares a considerable degree of similarity with the MoFe protein of nitrogenase (|FRAME: NifDK NifDK|). However, it contains |FRAME: CPD-7| (termed the O-cluster) instead of |FRAME: 8FE-7S| (P-cluster). The form of the protein that contains only |FRAME: CPD-7| is referred to as |FRAME: NifEN <i>apo</i>-NifEN|.
/
/The |FRAME: CPD-18407| precursor is passed from the |FRAME: NifB NifB protein| that produces it to the surface of |FRAME: NifEN <i>apo</i>-NifEN| |CITS: [21551100]|. It is held in place by at least an |FRAME: CYS| residue (Cys&alpha;25 in the protein from |FRAME: TAX-354|) |CITS: [21212358]|.
/Molybdenum is transferred by |FRAME: holo-NifQ NifQ|, which carries it as part of a different molybdenum-iron-sulfur cluster (which is only used as a molybdenum donor to the nitrogenase |FRAME: CPD-41|) |CITS: [18697929]|, and |FRAME: HOMO-CIT|, produced by |FRAME: G-44194 NifV|, is transferred by an unknown mechanism that involves NifH |CITS: [9294461]|.
/
/The resulting M-cluster is then relocated from the surface to the binding site within NifEN. In the enzyme from |FRAME: TAX-354| the M-cluster is held in its new place by interactions with Cys250 and Asn418, and the homocitrate is anchored by interactions with Arg402. The complex carrying the fully functional M-cluster is referred to as |FRAME: NifEN-M-cluster "a <i>holo</i>-NifEN"| |CITS: [21212358]|. 
/
/Despite the incomplete knowledge, it has clearly been shown that Mo and homocitrate are incorporated into the precursor while it is bound to NifEN, and that this cluster is transformed into a fully matured |FRAME: CPD-41| and inserted into its target location in the MoFe protein (the NifDK component of the nitrogenase complex) without the aid of a carrier or chaperone |CITS: [17050696]|.
/
/The structure shown below depicts Cys25, which interacts with the L-cluster, and Cys250 and Asn418, which interact with the M-cluster.
//
