UNIQUE-ID - PqsD
TYPES - Polypeptides
COMMON-NAME - a [PqsD protein]
COMMENT - PqsD from |FRAME: TAX-287| is a member of the FabH family of condensing enzymes that participates in the synthesis of the signal molecule |FRAME: CPD-12838| (see |FRAME: PWY-6660|) and of |FRAME: 4-hydroxy-2-1H-quinolone| (DHQ) , a molecule whose function is not yet known (see |FRAME: PWY-6661|).
/
/PqsD catalyzes the condensation of |FRAME: 2-AMINOBENZOYL-COA| (anthraniloyl-CoA) with |FRAME: MALONYL-COA|. The enzyme forms an acyl-enzyme intermediate with |FRAME: 2-AMINOBENZOYL-COA|, which then reacts with |FRAME: MALONYL-COA| to produce the short-lived thioester |FRAME: CPD-19113|. This compound forms a branch - in the absence of PqsE it is susceptible to spontaneous cyclization to form |FRAME: 4-hydroxy-2-1H-quinolone|. However, when PqsE is present, it removes the CoA moiety, forming |FRAME: CPD-19114| |CITS: [25960261]|.
/
/The enzyme activity was analyzed by TLC analysis of reaction mixtures containing |FRAME: MALONYL-COA| and [<sup>14</sup>C]|FRAME: 2-AMINOBENZOYL-COA|. Products were quantitated by LC-MS |CITS: [18728009]|.
/
/The crystal structure of recombinant wild-type and mutant enzymes has been determined. The protein was found to be a homodimer and has structural similarities to a variety of condensing enzymes including |FRAME: EG10277| from |FRAME:TAX-562| (see |FRAME: CPLX0-252|) |CITS: [19694421]|.
//
