UNIQUE-ID - apo-ACP
TYPES - ACP
TYPES - All-apo-ACPs
COMMON-NAME - a soluble <i>apo</i>-[acyl-carrier protein]
SYNONYMS - an apo-[acp]
SYNONYMS - an apo-[acyl-carrier protein]
SYNONYMS - fatty acid ACP
SYNONYMS - fatty acid acyl carrier protein
COMMENT - Acyl carrier proteins exist as either a distinct domain within a large multifunctional protein, or as discrete soluble single-domain proteins. This class describes the mall soluble acyl-carrier proteins that are found in bacteria and plant chloroplasts (such as type II FAS). Bacterial ACPs can also serve as acyl donors for synthesis of a variety of products, including endotoxin and acylated homoserine lactones involved in quorum sensing.
/
/This class does not include the |FRAME: Fatty-Acid-Synthase-ACPs "acyl-carrier proteins (ACPs) of eukaryotic fatty acid synthases"| (type I FAS), |FRAME: Polyketide-ACP-Proteins "ACPs of polyketide synthases"| (PKSs), and |FRAME: Peptidyl-Carrier-Proteins "peptidyl carrier proteins"| (PCPs) and |FRAME: Aryl-Carrier-Proteins "aryl carrier proteins"| of |FRAME: Non-ribosomal-peptide-synthetases "non-ribosomal peptide synthetases"| (NRPSs).
/
/Acyl-carrier proteins are synthesized in their |FRAME: All-apo-ACPs "<i>apo</i> inactive form"|, and are activated by attachment of a |FRAME: PANTETHEINE-P| moiety, removed from |FRAME: CO-A|, to an |FRAME: SER| residue, in a reaction catalyzed by |FRAME: EC-2.7.8.7| (4'-phosphopantetheinyl transferase) |CITS: [18059524]|.
ABBREV-NAME - an acyl-carrier protein
//
