UNIQUE-ID - PigG
TYPES - holo-Prolyl-carrier-proteins
COMMON-NAME - a <i>holo</i>-[PigG prolyl-carrier protein]
COMMENT - PigG is a peptidyl carrier protein from |FRAME: TAX-615| that is involved in the biosynthesis of the antibiotic |FRAME: CPD-16992|. It is homologous to the RedO protein of |FRAME: TAX-100226|, which participates in the conversion of L-proline to pyrrolyl-2-carboxyl-S-[peptidyl-carrier protein] during undecylprodigiosin biosynthesis |CITS: [11880032][15528645]|.
/
/A <i>pigG</i> null mutant was generated and found to have a white phenotype, indicating no production of pigment |CITS: [15853884]|. The mutant was shown to produce |FRAME: CPD-17007| (MAP), confirming that it is involved in the biosynthesis of |FRAME: CPD-17013| (MBC).
/
/The crystal structure of PigG has been resolved |CITS: [28258005]|.
//
