UNIQUE-ID - MTAC
TYPES - Cobalt-I-Corrinoid-Proteins
TYPES - Methanol-specific-corrinoid-proteins
COMMON-NAME - a [Co(I) methanol-specific corrinoid protein]
COMMENT - Methanogenesis from methanol begins with the formation of methyl-coenzyme M (CoM) from methanol
/and coenzyme M.
/An enzyme system composed of three polypeptides catalyzes this methyl transfer reaction;
/MtaB (formerly known as methyltransferase 1), MtaC, which binds a corrinoid prosthetic group |CITS: [9654068]|,
/and MtaA (formerly known as methyltransferase 2).
/MtaB and MtaC are known to form a tight heterodimeric complex. MtaB catalyzes the transfer of the
/methyl group from methanol to the corrinoid group bound to MtaC |CITS: [9057830]|. MtaA then transfers the methyl 
/group to coenzyme M |CITS:[6438059]|.
/It has been shown that MtaC can be subtituted by free cob(I)alamin |CITS: [10215883]|.
//
