COMMENT - |FRAME: Maackiain Maackiain| is a common pterocarpan that has been detected in many legumes. Within the two subtribes <i>Diocleinae</i> and <i>Erythrininae</i> it was found in 12 species representing 4 genera |CITS: [Ingham90]|. Maackiain was originally discovered in the |FRAME: TAX-37501| tree, which is named after its discoverer, the 19th-century Siberian explorer Karlovich Maack. Maackiain can be found in both a (-) and a (+) conformations. In chickpea, where it is a major pterocarpan phytoalexin together with medicarpin, it occurs exclusively in the (-) conformation |CITS: [8071365]|.
