UNIQUE-ID - LovF
TYPES - Polyketide-ACP-Proteins
COMMON-NAME - an <i>apo</i>-2-methylbutanoate polyketide synthase
SYNONYMS - LovF
COMMENT - LovF is a 277 kDa diketide synthase characrterized from the filamentous fungus |FRAME: TAX-33178| that is involved in the biosynthesis of |FRAME: CPD-16924 lovastatin|. LovF synthesizes the |FRAME: CPD-16943| side chain, which is subsequently transferred by the dissociated acyltransferase |FRAME: MONOMER-18785 LovD| to the C8-hydroxyl of |FRAME: CPD-16908| to yield the complete natural product, |FRAME: CPD-16924|.
/
/The enzyme utilizes acetyl-CoA, malonyl-CoA, NADPH, and SAM to yield |FRAME: 2-methylbutanoyl-LovF "<i>R</i>-methylbutanoyl-S-LovF"|, in a process that involves a single condensation reaction followed by &alpha;-methylation, &beta;-ketoreduction, dehydration, and &alpha;,&beta; enoyl reduction reactions at the active sites of the various catalytic domains |CITS: [21069965]|.
