COMMENT - Sphingoids (sphingoid bases, or long chain bases) are building blocks of |FRAME: SPHINGOLIPIDS sphingolipids|. They are amino alcohols, composed predominantly (but not exclusively) of 18 carbon atoms. They are characterized by the presence of a hydroxyl group at C1 (and often also at C3), and an amine group at C2. The commonly known sphingoids include |FRAME: SPHINGOSINE|, |FRAME: D-erythro-Shinganines sphinganine| (dihydrosphingosine), and |FRAME: Phytosphingosines phytosphingosine| (4-hydroxysphinganine).
