//
UNIQUE-ID - Delta-lactones
TYPES - Lactones
COMMON-NAME - a &delta;-lactone
COMMENT - A |FRAME: Lactones "lactone"| is a cyclic ester, the product of condensation of an alcohol group and a carboxylate group
/within the same molecule. It is characterized by a closed ring consisting of two or more carbon atoms and a single oxygen atom, with a ketone group connected to one of the carbons adjacent to the ring oxygen.
/
/There are several types of lactones - |FRAME: Beta-lactones| contain 3 carbons in the ring,
/|FRAME:Gamma-lactones| contains 4, |FRAME:Delta-lactones| contains 5, and |FRAME:Epsilon-lactones|
/contains 6 carbons.
//
UNIQUE-ID - NORLIGNANS
TYPES - PHENYLPROPANOID-SYN
COMMON-NAME - Norlignan Biosynthesis
COMMENT - This class contains pathways of biosynthesis of norlignans, which are natural occurring phenolic compounds with a diphenylpentane core skeleton being formed from a phenylpropane (C6C3) and an phenylethane unit (C6C2), linked via a C7-C8' bond and constituting the basic norlignan [C6-C3(C2)-C6] carbon scaffold. Norlignans are typical compounds in heartwood and also occur in herbaceous plants where they display a wide spectrum of bioactive properties of pharmaceutical importance. 
//
UNIQUE-ID - GLUTAREDOXIN-C
