UNIQUE-ID - DNA-deoxycytidine-dimer
TYPES - Nonadjacent-pyrimidine-dimer-in-DNA
COMMON-NAME - a dimer of non-adjacent 2'-deoxycytidines in DNA
SYNONYMS - cyclobutane_dCdC
COMMENT - Exposure of cells to ultraviolet light results in the formation of DNA photoproducts, the majority of which arise from a photoreaction between two pyrimidines. The structure and stereochemistry of the photoproducts depend on the conformation of the two bases at the time of irradiation. Irradiation of A form DNA generates |FRAME: CPD-11654 "spore photoproducts"|, while irradiation of B form DNA produces <i>cis</i>-<i>syn</i> cyclobutane pyridine dimers, |FRAME: CPD-11657 "pyrimidine (6-4) pyrimidone photoproducts"|, and their Dewar valence isomers |CITS: [15748634][30065996]|.
/
/The vast majority of pyrimidine dimers occurs from an interaction of two adjacent pyrimidine nucleotide. Non-adjacent photodimers of both intra-strand and inter-strand types are much rarer, but do occur, leading to UV-induced deletion mutations |CITS: [18680367]|.
//
UNIQUE-ID - Apo-EntB
TYPES - Apo-Aryl-Carrier-Proteins
COMMON-NAME - an <i>apo</i>-[EntB aryl-carrier protein]
COMMENT - EntB is a bifunctional enzyme that is involved in the |FRAME: ENTEROBACTIN| biosynthesis pathway. Enterobactin, a siderophore molecule, is synthesized in response to iron deprivation by formation of an amide bond between |FRAME: 2-3-DIHYDROXYBENZOATE| (2,3-DHB) and |FRAME: SER|.
/
/EntB is a bifunctional protein that consists of an N-terminal isochorismatase domain and a C-terminal aryl-carrier protein (ArCP) domain |CITS: [9214294]|. The isochorismatase domain catalyzes the synthesis of |FRAME: DIHYDRO-DIOH-BENZOATE| from |FRAME: ISOCHORISMATE| (|FRAME: EC-3.3.2.1|).
/
/The <i>apo</i>-ArCP domain first undergoes phosphopantetheinylation catalyzed by EntD, turning EntB into the active <i>holo</i>-EntB. The active domain then serves as a substrate for EntE, which activates |FRAME: 2-3-DIHYDROXYBENZOATE| (formed from |FRAME: DIHYDRO-DIOH-BENZOATE| by EntA) and attaches it to the ArCP domain of EntB |CITS: [9485415][9214294]|.
ABBREV-NAME - [EntB aryl-carrier protein]
