UNIQUE-ID - 16S-rRNAs
TYPES - rRNAs
COMMON-NAME - a 16S rRNA
COMMENT - The 16S ribosomal RNA is the RNA component of the 30S small subunit of the prokaryotic ribosome. The 3' end of the 16S rRNA contains the anti-Shine-Dalgarno sequence, which binds upstream to the AUG start codon on the mRNA. The 3'-end also binds to the S1 and S21 proteins, which are involved in initiation of protein synthesis.
/
/The gene encoding the 16S rRNA is used as the standard for building philogenetic trees for the classification and identification of microbes.
/
/
