UNIQUE-ID - Galactolipids
TYPES - GLYCOSYLGLYCERIDES
COMMON-NAME - a galactolipid
COMMENT - Galactolipids are the main lipids of the membranes of chloroplasts and photosynthetic microorganisms. The main galactolipids in these membranes are |FRAME: D-Galactosyl-12-diacyl-glycerols| (MGDG) and |FRAME: Galactosyl-galactosyl-diacyl-glycerols| (DGDG). These compounds have been found in the X-ray structures of photosynthetic complexes, and are believed to assume a direct role in photosynthesis |CITS: [11906834]|.
/
/The galactolipids |FRAME: D-galactosylceramide galactocerebrosides| and |FRAME: GALACTOSYLCERAMIDE-SULFATE "galactocerebrosides 3-sulfate"| are abundant components in myelin, the membrane around the axons in the nervous system of vertebrates |CITS: [9530920]|.
/
/In addition, some galactolipids act as secondary metabolites and herbivore deterrents in plants and algae |CITS: [1408943][11999395][12684854]|.
