COMMENT - The predominant long-chain base in animal ceramides is |FRAME: SPHINGOSINE|, which is only present in trace amount in plant ceramides.
/In contrast, |FRAME: CPD-13612|, |FRAME: PHYTOSPINGOSINE|, and |FRAME: CPD-10693| are the prevalent long-chain bases in plants. The acyl chain of plant ceramides contains &alpha;-hydroxylated very long chain fatty acids.
