SYNONYMS - a (4E)-sphing-4-enine ceramide
COMMENT - A |FRAME: N-Acylsphingosine "sphingosine ceramide"| is |FRAME: Ceramides| molecule that is composed of |FRAME: SPHINGOSINE| and |FRAME: Fatty-Acids|. This type of ceramide is common in animals, and is produced by desaturation of a sphinganine base within a ceramide (known as |FRAME: CPD3DJ-82|) by |FRAME: EC-1.14.19.17|.
/
/Ceramides are found in high concentrations within the cell membrane and are one of the component lipids that make up |FRAME: Sphingomyelins sphingomyelin|, one of the major lipids in the lipid bilayer.
//
