UNIQUE-ID - Neolacto-Series-GSLs
TYPES - Glycosphingolipids
COMMON-NAME - a neolacto-series glycosphingolipid
COMMENT - |FRAME: Glycosphingolipids Glycosphingolipids| are a family of complex lipids composed of |FRAME: Ceramides| and mono- or oligosaccharide moieties that play an important role in various cellular functions including recognition, cell adhesion, proliferation and differentiation |CITS: [8490246]|. The lipid portion is embedded in the outer plasma membrane leaflet and the sugar chains extended to the outer environment, acting as an antigen.
/
/Together with |FRAME: Glycoproteins glycoproteins| and |FRAME: Glycosaminoglycans glycosaminoglycans|, the glycosphingolipids contribute to the glycocalyx that covers eukaryotic cell surfaces.
/
/Glycosphingolipids are synthesized by the sequential addition of sugar residues to ceramide by glycosyltransferases that are specific to each glycosidic linkage.
/
/Glycoshphingolipids have been classified into the following 12 series based on their structure: |FRAME: Arthro-Series-GSLs arthro|, |FRAME: Gala-Series-GSLs gala|, |FRAME: Ganglio-Series-GSLs ganglio|, |FRAME: Globo-Series-GSLs globo|, |FRAME: Isoglobo-Series-GSLs isoglobo|, |FRAME: Lacto-Series-GSLs lacto|, |FRAME: Muco-Series-GSLs muco|, |FRAME: Mollu-Series-GSLs mollu|, |FRAME: Neogala-Series-GSLs neogala|, |FRAME: Neolacto-Series-GSLs neolacto|, |FRAME: Schisto-Series-GSLs schisto| and |FRAME: Spirometo-Series-GSLs spirometo| |CITS: [25969757]|.
/
/|FRAME: Lactosyl-Ceramides Lactosylceramide| is an important branching point, being a common precursor for the synthesis of the four major classes of glycosphingolipids: the |FRAME: Ganglio-Series-GSLs "ganglio series"|, the |FRAME: Lacto-Series-GSLs "lacto series"|, the |FRAME: Neolacto-Series-GSLs "neolacto series"|, and the |FRAME: Globo-Series-GSLs "globo series"| |CITS: [10320813]|.
/
/The core structure that defines the |FRAME: Neolacto-Series-GSLs "neolacto series"| is Gal&beta;(1,4)GlcNAc&beta;(1,3)Gal&beta;(1,4)Glc&beta;-Cer
/
/In the diagram below, R1 describes the variable part of the sphingoid base, R2 describes the fatty acid, and R3 describes the glycan moiety.
//
