COMMENT - Bisindole alkaloids is a general name for dimers of assorted |FRAME: STRICTOSIDINE| derivatives, formed by dimerization of the monomeric indole compounds (often |FRAME: Monoterpenoid-Indole-Alkaloids "monoterpene indole alkaloids"|. 
/
/More than 200 such compounds have been described.
