/
/The bitter acids consist of the so-called &alpha;- and &beta;-acids. The former group is of particular importance for the brewing industry as they are transformed into <i>iso</i>-&alpha;-acids such as |FRAME:CPD-7116| and  |FRAME:CPD-7115| during the brewing process, conferring the bitter taste of beer |CITS:[15953717]|.
