UNIQUE-ID - Class-IC-Cytochromes-C
TYPES - Class-I-Cytochromes-C
COMMON-NAME - a class IC <i>c</i>-type cytochrome
COMMENT - Class IC is for split-&alpha;-band cytochromes <i>c</i>.
/
/These cytochromes possess a widened or split &alpha; band of lowered absorptivity, which does not seem to correlate with dimerization.
/
/Sequence characteristics include -M - - - - - LS - - - I - - - - - Y- (sixth ligand region) and aromatic and proline residues after the heme binding site.
/
/Examples include the monomeric cytochrome <i>c</i><sub>6</sub> from Spirulina maxima; cytochrome <i>c</i>-554 from Thiobacillus neapolitanus; a pseudodimeric cytochrome <i>c</i>-554 from a halophilic Paracoccus strain, and a dihaem cytochrome <i>c</i><sub>4</sub> from Azotobacter vinelandii |CITS: [1646017]|.
