UNIQUE-ID - Saturated-Fatty-Acyl-CoA
TYPES - ACYL-COA
COMMON-NAME - a 2,3,4-saturated fatty acyl CoA
COMMENT - This class describes |FRAME:ACYL-COA "acyl-CoAs"| that do not contain any double bonds in the 2, 3, and 4 positions.
/Acyl-CoAs are oxoacids that have been activated by |FRAME: CO-A|. They are often classified by the length of their acyl moiety.
/
/This class includes the following sub-classes:
/
/|FRAME: Short-Chain-234-Saturated-acyl-CoAs "Short-chain 2,3,4-saturated fatty acyl-CoAs"| are derived from |FRAME: Short-chain-fatty-acids "2,3,4-saturated fatty acids with aliphatic chains shorter than 6 carbons"|.
/
/|FRAME: Medium-Chain-234-Saturated-acyl-CoAs "Medium-chain 2,3,4-saturated fatty acyl-CoAs"|  are derived from |FRAME: Medium-chain-fatty-acids "fatty acids with aliphatic chains of 6-12 carbons"|.
/
/|FRAME: Long-Chain-234-Saturated-acyl-CoAs "Long-chain 2,3,4-saturated fatty acyl-CoAs"| are derived from |FRAME: Long-Chain-234-Saturated-Fatty-Acids "2,3,4-saturated fatty acids with aliphatic chains of 13-22 carbons"|.
/
