UNIQUE-ID - TusA-L-cysteine
TYPES - PROT-CYS
COMMON-NAME - a [TusA]-L-cysteine
COMMENT - TusA is a sulfur/thiosulfate-carrier protein involved in many different functions, depending on the organism.
/
/In the Gram-negative bacterium |FRAME: TAX-562| TusA has a well documented function as a sulfurtransferase in tRNA modification and molybdenum cofactor biosynthesis |CITS: [23281480]|.
/
/In organisms that store sulfur globules such as |FRAME: TAX-1049| TusA functions in sulfur transfter during the globules degradation. It accepts a sulfur atom from a rhodanese-like protein and transfers it to |FRAME: DsrE-Protein| |CITS: [24648525]|.
/
/In the acidothermophilic sulfur- and tetrathionate-oxidizing archaeon |FRAME: TAX-1006005| TusA is also involved in thiosulfate transfer, accepting a thiosulfate group from |FRAME: MONOMER-19176| |CITS: [25122768]|.
//
