UNIQUE-ID - S-NEDD8-yl-NEDD8-E1-L-cysteine
TYPES - MOD-PROT-CYS
COMMON-NAME - an [E1 NEDD8-activating enzyme]-<i>S</i>-[NEDD8 protein]-yl-L-cysteine
COMMENT - NEDD8-activating enzymes, also known as E1 enzymes, catalyze the first step in the neddylation process. The E1 enzyme, which is a herodimeric complex, binds ATP-Mg<sup>2+</sup> and |FRAME: NEDD8| and catalyzes C-terminal acyl adenylation of NEDD8. A catalytic L-cysteine residue of the E1 enzyme then attacks the NEDD8-AMP complex through acyl substitution, creating a thioester bond and an AMP leaving group.
/
/This active form of NEDD8, bound to the E1 enzyme, is transferred to |FRAME: NEDD8-carrier-proteins-E2| through a transthioesterification reaction, in which an E2 catalytic L-cysteine attacks the backside of the E1-NEDD8 complex.
//
