UNIQUE-ID - CPD-538
TYPES - Amino-Acid-Derivatives
COMMON-NAME - a serine phosphoethanolamine
COMMENT - |FRAME: CPD-538 "Serine ethanolamine phosphate"| is found in the animal world in both of its stereoisomeric forms. The |FRAME: CPD-480 "L isomer"|, first isolated from muscle extracts of the river turtle (|FRAME: TAX-31138|) |CITS: [13211635]|, is present in and is believed to be restricted to the tissues of fish, amphibia, reptiles, and birds |CITS: [13743387]|. its function is as yet unknown |CITS: [14197386][14284710][5936240]|.
/
/The |FRAME: CPD-19125 "D isomer"| was first detected in and subsequently isolated from the tissues of the earthworm |CITS: [13820431]|, where it has been shown to be the precursor of the guanidino base, |FRAME: LOMBRICINE| |CITS: [14438943][14438944]|.
