SYNONYMS - a P histo-blood group antigen
SYNONYMS - T lymphocyte macrophage-associated antigen
SYNONYMS - TLMA
SYNONYMS - Gb4Cer
COMMENT - Originally, the name "globoside" was used as a generic name for the mucolipids present on human erythrocytes |CITS: [Yamakawa52]|. Later it was used for mucolipids possessing hexosamines as the only nitrogen-containing sugars. A structural analysis of the main component of the mucolipids identifed it as |FRAME: N-ACETYL-D-GALACTOSAMINYL-13-D-GALACT globotetraosylceramide| |CITS: [14002302][14002301]| and today the term globoside is a synonym for that compound.
/
/Globotetraosylceramide was characterized as a surface antigen produced by peripheral T cells (lymph node lymphocytes), previosuly known as T lymphocyte macrophage-associated antigen, or TLMA |CITS: [7430637]|.
