COMMON-NAME - a [PqsC protein]-<i>S</i>-octanoyl-L-cysteine
COMMENT - PqsC is a member of the FabH family of enzymes. The enzyme acquires an octanoyl group from |FRAME: CPD-196|, and attaches it to a cysteine residue (C129). Together with PqsB, the proteins catalyze the coupling of |FRAME: CPD-19114| with the octanoate group, resulting in decarboxylation and the closing of the quinoline ring |CITS: [24239007]|.
/
/Both PqsB and PqsC are required for the reaction. The proteins form a tight complex. Attempts to produce PqsC from |FRAME: TAX-287| individually in |FRAME: TAX-562| failed, but coexpression of both genes yielded active proteins. When copurified His-tagged PqsB and PqsC are analyzed on a native polyacrylamide gel, they produce one band even though their molecular weights differ |CITS: [24239007]|.
