COMMENT - |FRAME: CPD-7181 "Ganglioside GM3"| is a major glycosphingolipid in the plasma membrane and is widely distributed in vertebrates. It is known to participate in induction of differentiation |CITS: [6589019][3456169]|, modulation of proliferation |CITS: [2229037][6327695]|, maintenance of fibroblast morphology |CITS: [8999828]|, signal transduction |CITS: [9668338]|, and integrin-mediated cell adhesion |CITS: [1822242]|. It is also abundant in the membrane fraction of the fat globules of milk |CITS: [19674342]|.
/
/A nonsense mutation in the gene encoding GM3 synthase causes the human autosomal recessive infantile-onset symptomatic epilepsy syndrome |CITS: [15502825]|.
