UNIQUE-ID - ILE2-tRNAs
TYPES - ILE-tRNAs
COMMON-NAME - tRNA<sup>Ile2</sup>
SYNONYMS - TRNA(ILE2)
COMMENT - tRNA<sup>Ile2</sup> is an AUA codon-specific isoleucine tRNA. The unmodified tRNA<sup>Ile2</sup> bears the CAU anticodon, which is also found in tRNA<sup>Met</sup> responsible for AUG codon decoding.
/
/Archaeal tRNA<sup>Ile2</sup> with unmodified cytidine at position 34 is aminoacylated by methionyl-tRNA synthetase (MetRS) and deciphers the AUG codon, thus behaving like tRNAMet. Agmatinylation of that cytidine allows tRNA<sup>Ile2</sup> to read AUA instead of AUG |CITS: [20139989][22002222]|.
