COMMENT - |FRAME: CHITIN Chitin| is a polymer of repeating units of &beta;-(1,4)-linked |FRAME: N-ACETYL-D-GLUCOSAMINE| (GlcNAc)<sub>n</sub>. It may be the second most abundant biopolymer in the world, after cellulose. It is the main component of the cell walls of fungi, the exoskeletons of arthropods such as crustaceans and the insects, the radula of mollusks, and the beaks of the cephalopods.
/
/Chitin polymers have a high degree of polymerization and are insoluble in water |CITS: [20559485]|.
