SYNONYMS - &alpha;-D-glucopyranosyl-( 1->2)-D-glucopyranose
COMMENT - |FRAME: CPD-16569 Kojibiose| is a disaccharide that was initially characterized from koji extract [an extract produced from rice by the application of |FRAME: TAX-5062| (koji in Japanese) spores, an early step in the production of the Japanese liquor Sho-chu] |CITS: [Aso53]|, and later from hydrol |CITS: [13483572]|, honey |CITS: [13666886]| and dextrans |CITS: [13768213]|. Kojibiose is also found as a constituent of polysaccharides and the sugar chains of glycoproteins |CITS: [4149796]|. It can be produced from glucose by caramelization |CITS: [Sugisawa66]|.
/
/The structure, initially thought to be 3-<i>O</i>-&alpha;-D-glucopyranosyl-D-glucose, was shown to be 2-<i>O</i>-&alpha;-D-glucopyranosyl-D-glucose a few years later |CITS: [13483572]|. Crystalization was achieved in 1961 |CITS: [13787188]|.
