SYNONYMS - &alpha;-2,8-Linked polymer of sialic acid
SYNONYMS - an &alpha; 2,8-linked polymer of sialate
COMMENT - Polysialic acids are polymers of |FRAME: N-ACETYLNEURAMINATE "sialic acid"| and its derivatives. The degree of polymerization is 8 to 200 Sia residues.
/
/Polysialic acid is an unusual posttranslational modification that occurs on the neural cell adhesion molecules (NCAMs). In the synapse, the strong negative charge of the polysialic acid prevents NCAM cross-linking of cells.
