UNIQUE-ID - Fucoidans
TYPES - Sulfated-Polysaccharides
COMMON-NAME - a fucoidan
COMMENT - Fucoidan is a generic term used to describe sulfated polysaccharides (MW: average 20,000) found in various species of brown algae such as kombu (edible kelp from mostly the family |FRAME: TAX-33636|), limu moui (|FRAME: TAX-86906|), bladder wrack (|FRAME: TAX-49266|), wakame (|FRAME: TAX-74381|), mozuku (|FRAME: TAX-309737|), and hijiki (|FRAME: TAX-590727|).
/
/Fucoidan was first reported in 1913 under the name fucoidin |CITS: [Kylin13]|, but the name was changed in 1959 to  conform with polysaccharide nomenclature |CITS: [McNeely59]|.
/
/Fucoidan structure can be divided into two groups depending on their sources: one group includes |FRAME: TAX-33637| species that have their central chains composed by (1&rarr;3)-linked &alpha;-L-fucopyranose residues |CITS: [8408031]|; a second group includes fucoidan isolated from |FRAME: TAX-52968| and |FRAME: TAX-3011| species that have their central chains composed of repeating (1&rarr;3) and (1&rarr;4) linked &alpha;-L-fucopyranose residues |CITS: [11269406][21566795]|. Besides fucose and sulfate, the presence of monosaccharide residues such as mannose, galactose, glucose, xylose and uronic acids were also identified |CITS: [18794778]|.
/
/Several fucose-containing polymers with less than 90% fucosyl residues have also been reported from brown algae and some of them were given names: ascophyllan or xylofucoglycuronan, isolated from |FRAME: TAX-52969|, is based on a backbone of mannuronate with branches of 3-<i>O</i>-D-xylosyl-L-fucose-4-sulfate |CITS: [Larsen66][Kloareg86]|; sargassan or glycuronofucoglycan, also isolated from |FRAME: TAX-52969|, is based on linear chains of D-galactose with branches of L-fucose-3-sulfate or occasionally uronate |CITS: [Percival68][Medcalf78][Kloareg86]|. Other, generic names in use are F-fucoidan, which consists of mostly fucose |CITS: [23374164]|, U-fucoidan, which contains approximately 20% of glucuronic acid, and G-fucoidan, which contains a substantial amount of galactose |CITS: [20138103]|.
/
/Fucoidan has been reported to possess anti-tumoral |CITS: [Siddhanta01]|, anti-coagulant |CITS: [2804225][2620305][10882718][15962177]|, anti-viral |CITS: [2472775][15386190][9352294][Lapshina06]| and anti-inflamatory activities |CITS: [Siddhanta01]|. It is used mainly in the cosmetic industry, food industry, and biopharmaceutical industry |CITS: [Nagai03][20416671][Wijesinghe12]| and is also a popular cosmeceutical |CITS: [Kim08]|.
//
