UNIQUE-ID - Branched-truncated-alpha-1-6-mannans
TYPES - Mannans
COMMON-NAME - a branched &alpha;-(1,6)-D-mannan with truncated side chain
COMMENT - The mannan found in the cell walls of |FRAME: TAX-4932| is composed of a linear chain of |FRAME: Unbranched-1-6-Mannan "&alpha;-(1,6)-D-mannan"| decorated by side chains and attached to |FRAME: ASN| residues of proteins by a linkage unit consisting of two &beta;-(1,4)-<i>N</i>-acetylglucosamine residues.
/
/The composition of the side chains varies, but largely consists of &alpha;-(1,3)-mannosyl-&alpha;-(1,2)-mannosyl-&alpha;-(1,2)-mannosyl chains. The side chain can be shorter, and can be branched as well.
/
/This structure results from the action of |FRAME: EC-3.2.1.198|, which cleaves |FRAME: CPD-12789| off the side chains, leaving single &alpha;(1,2)-mannose residues attached to the backbone.
//
