COMMENT - |FRAME: L-glucose| does not occur naturally in higher organisms, and its production has been only rarely reported in microbes |CITS: [16233412]|. Several publications claimed that since it cannot be phosphorylated by hexokinase or glucokinase, it cannot be used as an energy source. However, there have been a few reports of bacterial |FRAME: CPD-3607| degradation |CITS: [40609][23038265]|.
/
/Each aldopentose or aldohexose exists as a mixture of at least six compounds: the aldehyde, the hydrated aldehyde
/(gem-diol), the two pyranoses, and the two furanoses. The open-chain structure shown here is provided only as a schematic illustration of chirality. Consult the appropriate class instances for information on specific ring structures and their anomeric configuration.
