SYNONYMS - GM1
SYNONYMS - GM1a
COMMENT - A ganglioside is a molecule composed of |FRAME: Glycosphingolipids| (|FRAME: Ceramides| and |FRAME: Oligosaccharides|) with one or more sialic acids (e.g. |FRAME: N-ACETYLNEURAMINATE|) linked on the sugar chain. Ganglioside are components of the cell plasma membrane that modulates cell signal transduction events, and appear to concentrate in lipid rafts.
/
/The name ganglioside is derived from ganglion cells of the brain, from which the first gangliosides were isolated by the German scientist Ernst Klenk in 1942. More than 60 gangliosides are known, which differ from each other mainly in the position and number of |FRAME: N-ACETYLNEURAMINATE| residues.
/
/The same four structures- |FRAME: CPD-7188 "ganglioside GM1|, |FRAME: N-ACETYLNEURAMINYL-ETCETERA-GLUCOSYLCERA "ganglioside GD1a"|, |FRAME: Ganglioside-GD1b "ganglioside GD1b"| and |FRAME: Ganglioside-GT1b "ganglioside GT1b"|, comprise the great majority of gangliosides in mammalian brains |CITS: [22735313]|.
/
/|FRAME: CPD-7188 "Ganglioside GM1"| (also known as ganglioside GM1a) is one of major gangliosides in vertebrate brain, and shows specific binding with cholera toxin B subunit, resulting in important biological events such as cAMP response |CITS: [1058471]|. GM1 is also involved in the receptor functions for peptide hormones such as follicle-stimulating hormone and luteinizing hormone |CITS: [185697]|.
//
