UNIQUE-ID - Peptidoglycan-with-crosslinks
TYPES - Peptidoglycans
COMMON-NAME - a peptidoglycan with cross-links
COMMENT - The strength of the peptidoglycan polymer is obtained by extensive cross-linking between the peptide side-chains that extend from the glycan strand.
/
/The cross-linking is formed by transpeptidases and occur within newly synthesized peptidoglycan polymers and between newly made material and preexisting peptidoglycan. Cross-links are also present between peptidoglycan and lipoproteins in the outer membrane.
/
/Common forms of cross-linking enzymes are the DD-transpeptidases that catalyze cross-linking between the D-alanine at position 4 of a pentapeptide side-chain and the <i>meso</i>-diaminopimeloyl or lysyl residue at position 3 of a different side-chain; and the LD transpeptidases, which catalyze the cross linking between two <i>meso</i>-diaminopimeloyl or lysyl residues of separate side-chains.
