SYNONYMS - a nucleotide diphosphate D-ribose
SYNONYMS - NDP-D-ribofuranose
SYNONYMS - NDP-ribose
COMMENT - While |FRAME: D-Ribofuranose| (D-Rib<i>f</i>) is present in the O antigens of several bacterial strains (such as the |FRAME: TAX-562| serogroups O5, O20, O54, O105, O114, O153, O178, O183 and O185), ribofuranose transfer reactions are not well characterized. The donor in these reactions is assumed to be a nucleotide diphosphate form, as is standard in this type of reactions, though this has not been verified.
/
/As of 2020 the existence of a nucleotide-activated ribofuranose has not been demonstrated in any bacterial strain, and genes responsible for its nucleotide precursor synthesis are not found in any O antigen gene cluster |CITS: [31778182]|. Studies of the biosynthesis of the D-ribofuranose donor in <i>Salmonella</i> suggested that it is not produced by a hexose to pentose conversion |CITS: [4926677]|. A ribofuranosyltransferase, named |FRAME: G-81106 WbaM|, was reported from |FRAME: TAX-621| |CITS: [15774901]|.
