UNIQUE-ID - Peptidoglycan-DD-crosslinks
TYPES - Peptidoglycan-with-crosslinks
COMMON-NAME - a peptidoglycan with D,D crosslinks
COMMENT - Transpeptidases cross link glycan strands within newly synthesized peptidoglycan polymers and between newly made material and preexisting peptidoglycan; they also link peptidoglycan to Braun's lipoprotein (Lpp) in the outer membrane and catalyze the exchange of carboxy terminal D-alanine residues with glycine in the peptide stem. 
/
/DD-transpeptidases catalyze the cross-linking of the glycan strands between the D-alanine at position 4 of a pentapeptide stem and the <i>meso</i>-diaminopimelyl or lysyl residue at position 3 of a different side-chain.
/
/LD transpeptidases catalyze the cross linking between two <i>meso</i>-diaminopimelyl or lysyl residues of separate side-chains.
//
