UNIQUE-ID - CPD-8594
TYPES - Lewis-Antigen
COMMON-NAME - a Lewis x epitope
SYNONYMS - &beta;-D-galactosyl-(1&rarr;4)-[&alpha;-L-fucosyl-(1&rarr;3)]-<i>N</i>-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-R
SYNONYMS - 1,4-&beta;-D-galactosyl-(&alpha;-1,3-L-fucosyl)-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-R
SYNONYMS - 1,4-&beta;-D-galactosyl-(&alpha;-1,3-L-fucosyl)-<i>N</i>-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-[glycoprotein]
SYNONYMS - a 1,4-&beta;-D-galactosyl-(&alpha;-1,3-L-fucosyl)-<i>N</i>-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-[glycoprotein]
SYNONYMS - a 1,4-&beta;-D-galactosyl-(&alpha;-1,3-L-fucosyl)-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-R
SYNONYMS - a &beta;-D-galactosyl-(1&rarr;4)-[&alpha;-L-fucosyl-(1&rarr;3)]-<i>N</i>-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-R
SYNONYMS - a histo-blood group Le<sup>x</sup> antigen
SYNONYMS - SSEA-1
SYNONYMS - stage-specific embryonic antigen 1
COMMENT - The |FRAME: CPD-8594 "Lewis x"| epitope, also known as stage-specific embryonic antigen-1 (SSEA-1) or CD15 |CITS: [281705]|, is a carbohydrate structure expressed on several glycolipids, glycoproteins, and proteoglycans of the nervous system and has been implicated in cell-cell recognition, neurite outgrowth, and neuronal migration during development. It appears to be involved in regulating neural stem cells via the Notch signaling pathway |CITS: [22645129]|.
/
/The |FRAME: CPD-8594 "Lewis X epitope"| is formed by &alpha;(1,3) fucosylation of the <i>N</i>-acetylglucosaminyl residue of |FRAME: B-Gal-14-NacGlc-R|, the disaccharide precursor that can also lead to formation of the |FRAME: Type-2-H-Antigen| by &alpha;(1,2) fucosylation at its terminal galactosyl residue.
/In mice the &alpha;-(1,3)-fucosyltransferase encoded by the |FRAME: HS10520| gene is the main contributor to the production of the |FRAME: CPD-8594 "Lewis x"| epitope |CITS: [16973732]|.
/
/The related |FRAME: Lewis-a-epitope| is formed by &alpha;(1,4) fucosylation of the <i>N</i>-acetylglucosaminyl residue of |FRAME: beta-Gal-13-beta-GlcNac-R|, which can also lead to formation of |FRAME: Type-1-H-Antigen| by &alpha;(1,2) fucosylation at its terminal galactosyl residue.
/
/Both the |FRAME: CPD-8594| and the |FRAME: Lewis-a-epitope| cannot be further transformed to ABH-type antigens |CITS: [6156588]|.
/
/The carbohydrate moiety of the Lewis x epitope is known as |FRAME: CPD-16475 CD15| (cluster of differentiation 15 antigen).
//
