UNIQUE-ID - Strychnos-MIAs
TYPES - Corynanthe-MIAs
COMMON-NAME - a strychnos-type monoterpenoid indole alkaloid
COMMENT - Strychnos-type monoterpenoid indole alkaloids includes those alkaloids in which an unrearranged monoterpenoid unit may be identified as being attached to the indole nucleus by C-2&ndash;C-16 and C-7&ndash;C-3 (or &ndash;C-21) bonds.
/
/These alkaloids are found only in species of the plant families Apocynaceae and Loganiaceae and are biogenetically formed via geissoschizine and preakuammicine, either directly from the latter (Strychnan skeletal type; C-7&ndash;C-3 bond) or via the intermediacy of stemmadenine-related iminium cations (Aspidospermatan skeletal type; C-7&ndash;C-21 bond)
//
