UNIQUE-ID - Short-Chain-234-Saturated-Fatty-Acids
TYPES - CPD66-39
TYPES - Short-chain-fatty-acids
COMMON-NAME - a short-chain 2,3,4-saturated fatty acid
COMMENT - |FRAME: Fatty-Acids "A fatty acid"| is a carboxylic acid with a long unbranched aliphatic tail. This class describes |FRAME: Fatty-Acids "fatty acids"| that do not contain any double bonds in the 2, 3, and 4 positions. The compounds in this class are often classified by the length of their aliphatic chains.
/
/|FRAME: Short-Chain-234-Saturated-Fatty-Acids "Short-chain 2,3,4-saturated fatty acids"| are 2,3,4-saturated fatty acids with aliphatic chains of less than 6 carbons.
/
/|FRAME: Medium-Chain-234-Saturated-Fatty-Acids "Medium-chain 2,3,4-saturated fatty acids"| are 2,3,4-saturated fatty acids with aliphatic chain of 6-12 carbons.
/
/|FRAME: Long-Chain-234-Saturated-Fatty-Acids "Long-chain 2,3,4-saturated fatty acids"| are 2,3,4-saturated fatty acids with aliphatic chains of 13-22 carbons.
/
/|FRAME: Very-Long-Chain-234-Saturated-FAs "Very-long-chain 2,3,4-saturated fatty acids"| are 2,3,4-saturated fatty acids with aliphatic chains of 23 carbons or longer.
//
