COMMENT - The |FRAME: Lewis-a-epitope "Lewis a epitope"| is formed by &alpha;(1,4) fucosylation of the <i>N</i>-acetylglucosaminyl residue of |FRAME: Core1|, the disaccharide precursor that can also lead to formation of the |FRAME: Type-1-H-Antigen| by &alpha;(1,2) fucosylation at its terminal galactosyl residue |CITS: [5691821]|.
