UNIQUE-ID - CPD-14577
TYPES - Plant-Arabinogalactans
COMMON-NAME - a plant arabinogalactan-[protein]
SYNONYMS - a plant [protein]-arabinogalactan
SYNONYMS - AGP
SYNONYMS - Arabinogalactan-proteins
COMMENT - Plant arabinogalactan-proteins belong to a large family of wall glycoproteins/proteoglycans, known as the Pro/Hyp-rich glycoproteins. They are found on the plasma membrane, in the wall, in the apoplastic space, and in secretions.
/
/The glycan moiety of these glycoproteins constitutes 90% to 98% of the weight. It usually consists of branched type II arabino-3,6-galactans, primarily <i>O</i>-linked to Hyp residues |CITS: [20388666]|.
/
/In general, the glycan moieties of plant arabinogalactan-proteins (AGPs) demonstrate a great structural and compositional variability. The structure shown here is based on a representative Hyp-AG polysaccharide (AHP-1) released by base hydrolysis from a synthetic AGP (Ala-Hyp)<sub>51</sub> from tobacco BY2 cells |CITS: [14724279]|.
//
