UNIQUE-ID - Antigen-ALey
TYPES - Lewis-Antigen
COMMON-NAME - an A (Lewis y) histo-blood group epitope
SYNONYMS - a blood group ALe<sup>y</sup> antigen
COMMENT - The Lewis y epitope (Le<sup>y</sup>) is a difucosylated oligosaccharide derived from |FRAME: B-Gal-14-NacGlc-R "type 2 precursor disaccharides"| carried by glycoconjugates on the cell surface. Le<sup>y</sup> is expressed predominately during embryogenesis, and expression on adult tissue is restricted to granulocytes and epithelial surfaces |CITS: [11037972]|, where it acts as a ligand for lectin-like proteins |CITS: [18711002][22101897]|. However, Le<sup>y</sup> is overexpressed in the majority of carcinomas, including breast, ovary, pancreas, prostate, colon, and non-small cell lung cancers, and has been correlated to the pathological staging and prognosis |CITS: [2537068][7714977][8621218][9824007][21512109]|. In these cases, Le<sup>y</sup> occurs either at the plasma membrane as a glycolipid or linked to surface receptors |CITS: [2436750][14871842]|.
/
/Le<sup>y</sup> was shown to play an important role in promoting cell proliferation, tumorigenecity and adhesion |CITS: [21152298][18205178]|, and several clinical trials were conducted using Le<sup>y</sup> monoclonal antibodies for targeted immunotherapy of tumors |CITS: [1327079][8577771][8640770][10829049][10861456][16963623][17545534][17909358][19825951][26026738]|.
/
/The human pathogenic bacterium |FRAME: TAX-210| is known to express the Le<sup>y</sup> antigen in its lipopolysaccharide, mimicking human cell surface glycoconjugates |CITS: [8890213][10096092][11237846][11741906]|.
//
UNIQUE-ID - Phospholipid-Cyclopropane-Fatty-Acids
