UNIQUE-ID - Phycobilins
TYPES - Phytobilins
COMMON-NAME - a phycobilin
COMMENT - Phycobilins are photosynthetic chromophores found in |FRAME: TAX-1117| and in the chloroplasts of |FRAME: TAX-2763 rhodophytes|, |FRAME: TAX-38254 glaucocystophytes|, and some |FRAME: TAX-3027 cryptomonads|, but not in green algae and higher plants. They are bound to soluble proteins called |FRAME: Phycobiliproteins phycobiliproteins|, which pass the light energy captured by the phycobillins to |FRAME: Chlorophylls chlorophylls|.
/
/The phycobilins are efficient at absorbing wavelengths that are not absorbed well by |FRAME: CHLOROPHYLL-A|, including red, orange, yellow, and green light. 
/
/The phycobilins are divided into four main types: |FRAME: Phycoerythrobilins phycoerythrobilins|, |FRAME: Phycourobilins phycourobilins|, |FRAME: Phycoviolobilins phycoviolobilins|, and |FRAME: Phycocyanobilins phycocyanobilins|.
/
