UNIQUE-ID - Man7GlcNAc2-protein-A123B3
TYPES - N-Glycans
COMMON-NAME - Man<sub>7</sub>(GlcNAc)<sub>2</sub>-[protein] (isomer 7A<sub>1,2,3</sub>B<sub>3</sub>)
SYNONYMS - an &alpha;-D-Man-(1&rarr;2)-&alpha;-D-Man-(1&rarr;2)-&alpha;-D-Man-(1&rarr;3)-[&alpha;-D-Man-(1&rarr;2)-&alpha;-D-Man-(1&rarr;3)-[&alpha;-D-Man-(1&rarr;6)]-&alpha;-D-Man-(1&rarr;6)]-&beta;-D-Man-(1&rarr;4)-&beta;-D-GlcNAc-(1&rarr;4)-&beta;-D-GlcNAc-1-L-asparaginyl-[protein]
SYNONYMS - a [(mannosyl)<sub>7</sub>(<i>N</i>-acetylglucosaminyl)<sub>2</sub>]-L-asparaginyl-[protein] (isomer 7A<sub>1,2,3</sub>B<sub>3</sub>)
COMMENT - This is one of four isomers of Man<sub>7</sub>GlcNAc<sub>2</sub> chains that are found in <i>N</i> glycans.
/
/The nomenclature used to identify high mannose glycans has not been standardized. Several earlier systems were insufficient to describe all possible isomers |CITS: [7954510][17719235][17685584]|. The nomenclature used here is that proposed by Prien et al |CITS: [19181540]|, which can represent all processing isomers.
/
/According to this nomenclature, the other three Man<sub>7</sub>GlcNAc<sub>2</sub> isomers are named |FRAME: Man7GlcNAc2-protein-A123B2 "isomer 7A<sub>1,2,3</sub>B<sub>2</sub>"|, |FRAME: Man7GlcNAc2-protein-A123B1 "isomer 7A<sub>1,2,3</sub>B<sub>1</sub>"| and |FRAME: Man7GlcNAc2-protein-A12B12 "isomer 7A<sub>1,2</sub>B<sub>1,2</sub>"|.
//
