SYNONYMS - a [glycerolipid]-(9Z,12R)-12-hydroxyoctadec-9-enate
COMMENT - |FRAME: CPD-12193 Ricinoleate| is an unsaturated &omega;-9 fatty acid (indicating the double bond is located 9 carbons from the methyl end of the molecule). It is a major component of the seed oil obtained from |FRAME: TAX-3988| (Castor bean) seeds. |FRAME: CPD-12193 Ricinoleate| is also a major component of he sclerotium (a compact mass of hardened fungal mycelium containing food reserves) produced by the ergot fungus (|FRAME: TAX-5111|).
/
/Like other fatty acids, |FRAME: CPD-12193| is rarely found in its free form. It is usually found either as |FRAME: CPD-15364| or |FRAME: CPD-17396 "incorporated into a lipid"|.
