UNIQUE-ID - CPD0-1185
TYPES - Peptidoglycan-LD-crosslinks
COMMON-NAME - a peptidoglycan internal segment with L,D cross links (<i>meso</i>-diaminopimelate containing)
COMMENT - This compound represents an internal segment of a peptidoglycan polymer (<i>meso</i>-diaminopimelate containing). It contains an L,D (or 3 &rarr;3) cross link formed between the L-centre of <i>meso</i>-DAP of a peptide on one glycan chain to the D-centre of <i>meso</i>-DAP from a separate glycan chain. The R groups represent glycan chains of &beta;1,4-linked N-acetylglucosamine and N-acetylmuramic acid residues with peptide stems of varying length (penta-, tetra- and tripeptide) - some of which may be involved in cross-links with other glycan strands.
/
/3 &rarr;3 cross-links are formed by L,D-transpeptidases. They are present in low abundance in |FRAME: TAX-562| although their proportion increases in stationary phase and under some stress conditions. Hydrolysis of cross-links is important for both peptidoglycan expansion and recycling, and is catalysed by endopeptidases of varying specificity (see |CITS: [18266855]|).
//
