TYPES - N-Glycans
COMMON-NAME - Man<sub>6</sub>(GlcNAc)<sub>2</sub>-[protein] (isomer 6A<sub>1,2</sub>B<sub>1</sub>)
SYNONYMS - an &alpha;-D-Man-(1&rarr;3)-[&alpha;-D-Man-(1&rarr;3)-[&alpha;-D-Man-(1&rarr;2)-&alpha;-D-Man-(1&rarr;6)]-&alpha;-D-Man-(1&rarr;6)]-&beta;-D-Man-(1&rarr;4)-&beta;-D-GlcNAc-(1&rarr;4)-&beta;-D-GlcNAc-1-L-asparaginyl-[protein]
SYNONYMS - [(mannosyl)<sub>6</sub>(<i>N</i>-acetylglucosaminyl)<sub>2</sub>]-L-asparaginyl-[protein] (isomer 6A<sub>1,2</sub>B<sub>1</sub>)
COMMENT - This is one of three isomers of Man<sub>6</sub>GlcNAc<sub>2</sub> chains that are found in <i>N</i> glycans.
/
/The nomenclature used to identify high mannose glycans has not been standardized. Several earlier systems were insufficient to describe all possible isomers |CITS: [7954510][17719235][17685584]|. The nomenclature used here is that proposed by Prien et al |CITS: [19181540]|, which can represent all processing isomers.
/
/According to this nomenclature, the other two Man<sub>6</sub>GlcNAc<sub>2</sub> isomers are named |FRAME: Man6-GlcNAc2-protein-A12B2 "isomer 6A<sub>1,2</sub>B<sub>2</sub>"| and |FRAME: Man6GlcNAc2-protein-A123 "isomer 6A<sub>1,2,3</sub>"|.
