COMMENT - According to the nomenclature used for hybrid and complex <i>N</i>-glycans, this compound is known as 26,24. The name is derived from having two <i>N</i>-acetylglucosaminyl residues attached by &beta;1-2 and &beta;1-6 linkages to the &alpha;-Man-(1&rarr;6) arm of the three mannose core, and two <i>N</i>-acetylglucosaminyl residues attached by &beta;1-2 and &beta;1-4 linkages to the &alpha;-Man-(1&rarr;3) arm |CITS: [24178944]|.
