UNIQUE-ID - L-Iduronate
TYPES - Iduronate
COMMON-NAME - L-iduronate
COMMENT - |FRAME: L-Iduronate| is a reducing acidic sugar that can form a ring structure, as shown for |FRAME: CPD-12515|. |FRAME: CPD-12515| is the major uronic acid component of the glycosaminoglycans |FRAME: Dermatan-Sulfate| and |FRAME: HEPARIN|. It is also present in |FRAME: Heparan-Sulfate|, but in a minor amount relative to its carbon-5 epimer |FRAME: GLUCURONATE|.
/
/|FRAME: CPD-12515|  is often modified by the addition of an O-sulfate group at carbon position 2 to form |FRAME: CPD-12518|.
/
/The open-chain structure shown here is provided only as a schematic illustration of chirality. Consult the appropriate class instances for information on specific ring structures and their anomeric configuration.
