UNIQUE-ID - CPD-16768
TYPES - Hexosamines
COMMON-NAME - mycosamine
SYNONYMS - 3-amino-3-desoxy-D-rhamnose
SYNONYMS - 3-amino-3,6-dideoxymannose
SYNONYMS - 3-amino-3,6-dideoxy-D-mannose
COMMENT - |FRAME: CPD-16768 Mycosamine| (3-amino, 3-6 dideoxy D-mannose) is the amino sugar present in polyene macrolide antibiotics, represented by |FRAME: Candicidins|, |FRAME: CPD-17211|, |FRAME: CPD-17212| and |FRAME: CPD-17213|. The amino sugar component mycosamine plays a critical role in conferring the antifungal properties exhibited by polyene antibiotics |CITS: [9380018][16045354]|.
/
/Mycosamine is synthesized in a GDP-activated form from the primary metabolite |FRAME: GDP-MANNOSE|.
