UNIQUE-ID - Chrysolaminarin
TYPES - 1-3-beta-D-Glucans
TYPES - 1-6-beta-D-Glucan
COMMON-NAME - chrysolaminarin
SYNONYMS - leucosin
COMMENT - Chrysolaminarin is a linear polymer of (1&rarr;3) and (1&rarr;6) &beta;-linked D-glucose units in a ratio of 11:1 |CITS: [13688276]|.
/
/Chrysolaminarin is a storage polysaccharide typically found in photosynthetic |FRAME: TAX-33634| (heterokonts). It is used as a carbohydrate food reserve by phytoplankton such as |FRAME: TAX-2836| (diatoms), and is one of the most common biopolymers in the world.
//
