COMMENT - According to the nomenclature used for hybrid and complex <i>N</i>-glycans, this compound is known as 2M<sub>5</sub>hy. The name is derived by having an <i>N</i>-acetylglucosaminyl residue added to a five mannose core (M5 core) by a &beta;1-2 linkage. The term "hy" indicates that this is a hybrid <I>N</i>-glycan. Hybrid <I>N</i>-glycans are defined by having only mannosyl (Man) residues on the &alpha;-Man-(1&rarr;6) arm and only <i>N</i>-acetylglucosaminyl (GlcNAc) residues on the &alpha;-Man-(1&rarr;3) arm |CITS: [24178944]|.
