UNIQUE-ID - 2-4-2-N-linked-Glycan
TYPES - N-Glycans
COMMON-NAME - a {&beta;-D-GlcNAc-(1&rarr;2)-&alpha;-D-Man-(1&rarr;3)-[&beta;-D-GlcNAc-(1&rarr;2)-&alpha;-D-Man-(1&rarr;6)]-[&beta;-D-GlcNAc-(1&rarr;4)]-&beta;-D-Man-(1&rarr;4)-&beta;-D-GlcNAc-(1&rarr;4)-&beta;-D-GlcNAc}-<i>N</i>-Asn-[protein]
SYNONYMS - [(2),(4),(2)]-<i>N</i>-linked glycan
SYNONYMS - bis-2,2 <i>N</i>-glycan
COMMENT - According to the nomenclature used for hybrid and complex <i>N</i>-glycans, this type of struc ture is known as bis-2,2.
/The term "bis" refers to structures with a bisecting <i>N</i>-acetylglucosaminyl (GlcNAc) residue, which is not attached to either the &alpha;-Man-(1&rarr;6)- or &alpha;-Man-(1&rarr;3)- arms of the three-mannose core,  but directly to the mannosyl residue which is attached to the &beta;-GlcNAc-(1&rarr;4)-&beta;-GlcNAc-Asn-[protein] moiety. Bisecting residues are added by |FRAME: EC-2.4.1.144|.
/
/The rest of the name is derived from having one <i>N</i>-acetylglucosaminyl residues attached by a &beta;1-2 linkage to the &alpha;-Man-(1&rarr;6) arm of the three mannose core, and one <i>N</i>-acetylglucosaminyl residue attached by a &beta;1-2 linkage to the &alpha;-Man-(1&rarr;3) arm |CITS: [24178944]|.
