SYNONYMS - Clostridium thermoaceticum
SYNONYMS - Clostridium thermaceticum corrig. Fontaine et al. 1942 (Approved Lists 1980)
SYNONYMS - Clostridium thermaceticum
COMMENT - |FRAME: TAX-1525| is a strictly anaerobic Gram-positive acetogenic bacterium. It uses electrons from different substrates to reduce |FRAME: CARBON-DIOXIDE| to |FRAME: ACET| by the |FRAME: CODH-PWY Wood-Ljungdahl| pathway. Since acetate is the only product of the pathway, the organism is considered a homoacetogen.
/
/However, |FRAME: TAX-1525| can use electron acceptors other than |FRAME: CARBON-DIOXIDE|, such as |FRAME: NITRATE|, |FRAME: NITRITE|, |FRAME: S2O3|, and |FRAME: DMSO|. Under most conditions, nitrate reduction occurs preferentially to |FRAME: CARBON-DIOXIDE| reduction.
